    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dclgs-second-statement-of-new-regulation"/>
    <title>DCLG's second statement of new regulation</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary/>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Second Statement of New Regulation is a forward look of all regulations (including measures which are deregulatory) being introduced by the Department which impact on businesses. They are scheduled to come into force between 1 July and 31 December 2011.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is published every six months to give businesses an indication of when regulations affecting them will be coming into effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The headline figures show:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the measures we are introducing this year will reduce burdens on businesses by an estimated £4.26 million per year&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;of the five measures we are introducing, three measures are estimated to have net cost savings to business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
