  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/11228</id>
    <published>2010-07-08T01:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-14T12:31:20+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dclg-structural-reform-plan"/>
    <title>DCLG structural reform plan</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Action plan for the Department for Communities and Local Government and monthly implementation updates.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This new action plan marks a radical shift of power from Whitehall to local councils and communities that will make the Big Society part of every day life. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The plan sets out a new programme for the Department for Communities and Local Government that will deliver radical decentralising and transparency reforms that put citizens and councils in control of their communities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is one of the first fundamental structural reform plans for making departments accountable for the implementation of the reforms set out in the coalition agreement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
